EP
For decimal rule:

We only need:

One decimal inside range (e.g., 50.5)
Maybe one near boundary (e.g., 1.1)
That’s enough.

Because decimals are one equivalence class.

Requirement:

Between 1 and 100 inclusive
Whole numbers only
Required
We can divide inputs into partitions:

Valid Partitions
1️⃣ Whole numbers between 1 and 100

Invalid Partitions
2️⃣ Whole numbers less than 1
3️⃣ Whole numbers greater than 100
4️⃣ Decimal numbers
5️⃣ Non-numeric input
6️⃣ Empty input

Each partition should behave consistently.

So:

If one decimal like 1.5 fails correctly,
then 2.7, 50.9, 99.1 should also fail.

They are all part of the same partition: “decimal values.”

That’s why we don’t test 20 decimals.